This article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Barack Obama on May 21, 2012. The memorandum designates the officers of the Millennium Challenge Corporation (MCC) to act as the Chief Executive Officer (CEO) of the MCC in the event that the CEO is unable to perform their duties. The order of succession is outlined, with the Deputy Chief Executive Officer being the first in line, followed by other officers in the listed order. The memorandum also includes exceptions and provisions for the President to depart from this order. It clarifies that the memorandum does not create any legally enforceable rights or benefits. The memorandum concludes by authorizing its publication in the Federal Register.